# /etc/ubongo/egress.hosts — the enumerable answer to "what can leave the
# machine" (ADR-0017). One hostname per line. refresh-egress.sh resolves
# these into the nftables allowlist on a 15-minute timer.
#
# Add each MCP server's host here when you enable it in settings.yaml —
# deliberately and visibly, in the same change. Loopback never needs a line.

# Every model and embedding call (LiteLLM → OpenRouter):
openrouter.ai

# The Telegram bot channel (v0.5 phase 04), when `ubongo telegram` is running.
# Remove this line if you don't run the Telegram bot.
api.telegram.org

# The Signal channel (v0.7). It is the signal-cli *daemon* (not Ubongo) that
# reaches these — the daemon runs inside the envelope, so its hosts are the
# enumerable answer (ADR-0024/0017). Remove these lines if you don't run Signal.
chat.signal.org
storage.signal.org
cdn.signal.org
cdn2.signal.org
cdn3.signal.org
